  02 Mar 2012; Naohiro Aota <naota@gentoo.org> spork-0.9.0.ebuild:
  Add ~x86-fbsd

*spork-0.9.0 (28 Jan 2012)

  28 Jan 2012; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +spork-0.9.0.ebuild:
  Version bump. Add ruby19. Stop trying to run the cucumber features since
  their setup is very brittle.

*spork-0.8.5 (16 Jan 2012)

  16 Jan 2012; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +spork-0.8.5.ebuild:
  Version bump. Avoid running rails-specific tests since they fail with Rails
  3.x installed.

  29 Dec 2011; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> spork-0.8.4-r1.ebuild:
  Add x86 keyword.

  09 Oct 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> spork-0.8.4-r1.ebuild:
  Depend on rspec-1.

  09 Oct 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -spork-0.8.4.ebuild:
  Remove old version.

*spork-0.8.4-r1 (26 Sep 2010)

  26 Sep 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +spork-0.8.4-r1.ebuild:
  Add ree18 target. Add missing dependency.

*spork-0.8.4 (11 Jul 2010)

  11 Jul 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +spork-0.8.4.ebuild,
  +metadata.xml:
  Initial import. Dependency of forthcoming rspec-2 and useful tool in its
